  "texts": [
    "The model might generate responses that seem plausible but lack a factual basis [22].",
    "This challenge ties into its second limitation, its knowledge cut-off point in September 2021.",
    "This means that any information or developments after that date may be unknown to the model, leading to potentially inaccurate or outdated information [23].",
    "Moreover, ChatGPT can be influenced by populism and political activism, reflecting biases in its training data and potentially echoing controversial perspectives, especially in political or social matters, thus raising concerns about its objectivity [24].",
    "The trustworthiness of ChatGPT may be questionable in controversial situations, such as the COVID-19 pandemic [25]."
